OL,7,FMr Henry described it as a
OL,8,F"victimisation" of his client and
OL,9,Fasked Mr Parker if he rejected it, to
OL,10,Fwhich he responded: "Unless I have got
OL,11,Fall the facts at my disposal ... I
OL,12,Fdon't think you can expect me to
OL,13,Fdeliver a black and white response on
OL,14,Fthis."
OL,16,FHe added: "I'm no longer obviously at
OL,17,Fthe Post Office which precludes me a
OL,18,Flittle bit from knowing what all the
OL,19,Fbackground is."
